content: Yeah, that sounds about right. I'm thinking I'll probably take the same route I take by train, so I'll still have to deal with the construction on Main Street. But at least on a bike, I'll have more control over my route and can try to find a way to avoid the worst of the construction. By the way, speaking of my train commute, I take the 7:15 AM train from my local station, which takes 25 minutes to reach the train station near my office.
